<br>
Warrior Pets.  Because of agro rules forcing any npc to choose a nearby players over any pet they only act as tanks when no REAL tank is present or on the job.<br>
<br>
They also don't infringe on what makes the class special by using discs or aa skills granted to warriors.<br>
<br>
Rogue pets.  Rogue pets actually compare too well to rogues damage wise however rogue damage is getting upgraded anyway.<br>
<br>
Rogue pets DO infringe on the rogue class by backstabbing unfortunately but they don't get to sneak/hide, poison, steal, or use duelist.<br>
<br>
Wizard Pets.  Until this change on test they sucked too much for anyone to care.   While they wont neccesarily improve dps enough for anyone to care even when they do have manna, which remains to be seen as its spell list could be trimmed which would result in more nukes and better dps I haven't seen any hard long parses on its damage yet anyway.  So until hard data is presented either argument for or against it is moot.<br>
<br>
The fact that casting spells that are special to the wiz class is worth adressing though.<br>
<br>
SUGGESTIONS<br>
<br>
-The fire pet should have a recast time equal to the time required for the pet to use its manna up + med to full making the reclaim strategy useless.<br>
<br>
-Ice Comet should be removed from its spell list out of respect for the wizard class.<br>
<br>
-It shouldn't AE at all if mobs are mezzed nearby or it shouldn't AE at all.<br>
<br>
-It shouldn't cast lures because unresisable nukes are the domain of wizards alone.<br>
<br>
-It shouldn't randomly snare/root mobs as this is basicly useless to the mage anyway.<br>
<br>
-It shouldn't cast damage shields in mid combat as this is dumb.<br>
<br>
-The nukes it has available to it may have to be adjusted based on the fact that it will cast them more often as it has less choices available.<br>
<br>
-Pet nuke damage should be nerfed in pvp to some percentage as a FM fire pet used to attack a player would be too powerful (not that anyone cares about pvp)<br>
<br>
btw...<br>
<br>
ADJUSTING A SKILL/ABILITY/SPELL OR VARIENT THEROF ONLY AVAILABLE ON TEST IS NOT A NERF!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elyia>Elyia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 274<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/20/03 1:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pets</span><hr size=1> I want a familiar that randomly summons me mod rods. Only we'll rename the spell and call it Familar's Gift.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :x --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/sick.gif ALT=":x"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
