<br>
Not to mention that despite the ignorant comments of mages about our limited use of Ice Comet 60+, Ice Comet is OUR BABY.  That particle effect is part of the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>little bit</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of wow-factor and satisfaction that wizards get.  We work our asses off being the most pitiful class in the game for 49 levels just so we can finally know glory by casting the spell with the greatest spell-effect in the game.  For sheer pride Ice Comet is a spell that defines wizards for ~60 levels of a game; the dream of one day being able to cast it, and then the 10 levels of being able to viably use it in many situations as a source of damage.  It's one of our best cold-based spells thru level 65.  Just 'cause it may slip out of our regular repertoire post-60 doesn't mean it doesn't have a place in the Wizard Hall-of-Fame of most-loved spells by wizards.  We love our Ice Comet, it's our precious, you can't have it!!!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The only other spell I disagree with is Atol's.  No snare for mages.  And if they do get an AoE snare, I hope the damn pet chain-casts Atol's when it's in melee range, snaring himself, and hopefully also his master.<br>
<br>
Upgrade the pet, but don't do this to wizards. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
